article.headline: Idaho 72, South Dakota State 67
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Trevor Morris scored 16 points off the bench Saturday to lead Idaho to a 72-67 win over South Dakota State. Kenoi Watson gave Idaho the lead for good on a layup with 42.6 seconds left. South Dakota State's Garrett Callahan's 3-point attempt then hit the front of the rim and Idaho pulled away. Five Vandals finished in double figures with Watson and Darin Nagle scoring 14 points each. Clyde Johnson had 13 and David Jackson added 10. Matt Cadwell led South Dakota State with 19 points. The Vandals (2-10) opened with a 9-2 run and led by as much as nine points before the Jackrabbits (4-11) put together an 18-0 run to take a nine-point lead of their own. South Dakota State hit four 3-pointers during the run, while Mackenzie Casey and Cadwell tallied five points each during the spurt. Casey finished with two of the Jackrabbits' seven first half 3-pointers. The teams combined to drain 12 first-half treys, with South Dakota State connecting on 7-of-9 opportunities to take a four-point halftime lead. Idaho regained the lead when Trevor Morris nailed a 3 with 13:22 left. Morris led the Vandals' comeback with eight points in a 3 minute, 30 second span. South Dakota State managed to tie the score four times after that, but never took regained the lead. The final deadlock came with 1:08 left after Cadwell scored in the lane. Callahan finished with 14 for the Jackrabbits, whose Nov. 16 loss to Idaho was the Vandals only other win this season.
